"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-keely-hodgkinson-paris-2024-athletics-olympics-b2592258.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Keely Hodgkinsonhas said becoming a poster girl for track and field would be an honour, as her coach called her a \\\"superstar\\\" who is ready to take on golden girl status.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-oldbecame an Olympic champion in the women's 800 metresin Paris on Monday evening, shrugging off the weight of enormous expectations to claim the gold.\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997612576, \"rank\": 2.389470994412807e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It makes her the first British woman to claim Olympic 800-metre gold since DameKelly Holmesin Athens in 2004, and the third going back to Ann Packer in 1964.\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ann_Packer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.5359858553975735e-31, \"text\": \"Ann Packer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ann_Packer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ann_Packer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On TuesdayTeam GBfought for more medals, with silver forJosh Kerrin the men's 1500 metres and silver at the velodrome for cyclists Jack Carlin, Ed Lowe and Hamish Turnbull in the men's team sprint.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Keirin_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kerrin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Keirin_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_National_Keirin_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.9982227858285151, \"rank\": 0.001479056752322772, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Carlin\", \"score\": 0.9999999796864361, \"rank\": 2.031349438779647e-08, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Carlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Carlin\"}, {\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ed_Lowe_(businessman)\", \"score\": 0.7159090621732908, \"rank\": 0.39682539682535223, \"text\": \"Ed Lowe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ed_Lowe_(businessman)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ed_Lowe_(businessman)\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Turnbull\", \"score\": 0.9999996070519818, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamish Turnbull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Turnbull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Turnbull\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teenage skateboarderSky Brownsecured bronze despite a shoulder injury and there was bronze for boxer Lewis Richardson after what he said was a \\\"devastating\\\" defeat in the men's 71kg semi-final.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Richardson_(Hollyoaks)\", \"score\": 0.9965136461602875, \"rank\": 0.0034965034965027397, \"text\": \"Lewis Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Richardson_(Hollyoaks)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Richardson_(Hollyoaks)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hodgkinson told the PA news agency she was \\\"over the moon\\\" about her success, adding: \\\"You can work so hard sometimes and it all not be executed as well as you like it to be.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1235, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am so happy I finally got my gold medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hodgkinson, from Atherton,Greater Manchester, has been dreaming of gold since the Tokyo Games where she claimed silver.\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Atherton\", \"score\": 0.9999899084054847, \"rank\": 1.009169604995421e-05, \"text\": \"Atherton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Atherton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Atherton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said: \\\"I think it was always an aim by Paris to try and be in a position to upgrade that to gold, and after so many silver medals in a global stage in my sport\\u2026 this one really meant the most and there is no better place to do it than theOlympicsto upgrade.\\\"\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1619, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997612576, \"rank\": 2.389470994412807e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athlete did not balk when asked if she was aiming for domination in the field, saying: \\\"Why not?\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why not aim high, see what else is out there?\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I still do not have a world championship gold, so there is still plenty more to be done.\\\"\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On potentially becoming a poster girl for the sport, Hodgkinson told PA: \\\"I think that's such a privileged position to be in.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2131, \"end\": 2141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I'd love for people to see me that way, it's such an honour.\\\"\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her strength and conditioning coach Dane Mitchell said Hodgkinson was made for the added attention that will come her way after her gold medal, insisting she is a \\\"superstar\\\".\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2308, \"end\": 2316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.429220641991148e-12, \"text\": \"Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\"}, {\"begin\": 2322, \"end\": 2332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Mitchell, who has worked with Hodgkinson for around five years, watched the race on TV from home and was \\\"pretty gutted\\\" not to be in Paris.\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.429220641991148e-12, \"text\": \"Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\"}, {\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2581, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997612576, \"rank\": 2.389470994412807e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The head of strength and conditioning at Leeds Beckett University told PA: \\\"(I am) absolutely over the moon for her, really.\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2630, \"end\": 2654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds_Beckett_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leeds Beckett University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds_Beckett_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds_Beckett_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, so proud of her.\\\"\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said one of his first reactions after her race was relief because there had been \\\"so much pressure\\\" for her.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I did know, deepest, deep down, I knew that if there was anyone who could cope with the pressure and rise to those big occasions, it is Keely,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 3007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew she would do it, but it's just brilliant to actually do it, you know, it's on paper: Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3119, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's still sinking in, it's incredible.\\\"\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said he was \\\"sweating\\\" and out of his seat shouting at his TV during the race.\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just really was hoping she executed what she's capable of and she did,\\\" Mr Mitchell said.\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3323, \"end\": 3331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.429220641991148e-12, \"text\": \"Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She really controlled the race.\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a masterclass, really, in tactical racing.\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was just so pleased when she crossed that line, and just to see her face, I nearly welled up, to be honest.\\\"\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The coach spoke a few weeks ago with Hodgkinson's father Dean, who told him: \\\"We think it's her time this time round,\\\" and Mr Mitchell said he felt the same.\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3573, \"end\": 3583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 3593, \"end\": 3597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.999999995057351, \"rank\": 2.6268070412119135e-09, \"text\": \"Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\"}, {\"begin\": 3662, \"end\": 3670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.429220641991148e-12, \"text\": \"Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has yet to speak to the Olympian, conscious of the whirlwind she will be caught up in, but texted her to say: \\\"Do not worry about me, enjoy it, and we will speak soon.\\\"\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked if Hodgkinson was ready for golden girl status, Mr Mitchell told PA: \\\"I think a lot of that was on her anyway.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3877, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 3925, \"end\": 3933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.429220641991148e-12, \"text\": \"Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I mean, she was thrust into that in 2021 after Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3986, \"to\": 4040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4034, \"end\": 4039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9986700606903506, \"rank\": 0.0012614163845978655, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 19, her life changed massively and I know it will change probably again, it will increase in intensity all the opportunities that come her way and things like that but I think she's ready for it.\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really do.\", \"from\": 4240, \"to\": 4252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It sounds cliche, sounds like Louis Walsh, but she literally thinks like a superstar and she looks like a superstar and she performs like a superstar.\", \"from\": 4254, \"to\": 4405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4285, \"end\": 4296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4296980161381003e-31, \"text\": \"Louis Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She is a superstar.\", \"from\": 4407, \"to\": 4427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She already was.\", \"from\": 4428, \"to\": 4444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's made for it.\\\"\", \"from\": 4445, \"to\": 4464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hodgkinson told BBC's 5 Live Breakfast that she will celebrate her Olympic gold with a glass of wine on the beach when she joins her family on holiday in Marbella in a few days.\", \"from\": 4466, \"to\": 4643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4466, \"end\": 4476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.996162264266641, \"rank\": 0.003852520689475186, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 4482, \"end\": 4485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9864909712956762, \"rank\": 0.012173608978850762, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She revealed that she was \\\"more of a rose wine girl\\\" than a cocktail girl and said: \\\"I will be on the beach at some point having a nice glass of rose wine.\\\"\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She jokingly promised to wear the gold medal on the beach in Spain, adding: \\\"I will snap a picture.\\\"\", \"from\": 4803, \"to\": 4903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her school friend, Manchester United and England footballer Ella Toone, was among those sharing congratulations after her race.\", \"from\": 4905, \"to\": 5032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4924, \"end\": 4941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_United_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9999999986835064, \"rank\": 1.3092022368964267e-09, \"text\": \"Manchester United\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_United_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_United_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 4946, \"end\": 4953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.623706554184346, \"rank\": 0.5195641920948546, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4965, \"end\": 4975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ella_Toone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ella Toone\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ella_Toone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ella_Toone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Toone shared a video of herself watching the final on TV, waving her hands in the air and jumping up and down when her school friend won.\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5171, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Congratulations Keely, just been screaming at the telly,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 5173, \"to\": 5241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So proud of you, everyone was rooting for you back home, you have done us all proud.\\\"\", \"from\": 5242, \"to\": 5328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 5330, \"to\": 5560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5381, \"end\": 5392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.854430993396946e-21, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"